# MVP System Design

## Aim
This document aims to write down the key system design idea for our thin, simple MVP

The MVP will allow a user to:
- Search for a film from an external database
- Mark it as watched
- Rate the film out of 100
- See their watched films

## High Leveel Components

### UI
The UI is the front end and is what hte user interacts with. The UI will allow a user to:

- allow users to search for films from an external database
- display search results
- allow users to add watched films to their film history
- allow users to rate films
- display watched films along with their ratings

## Backend API
This is a middle layer that primarily does orchestration. This is a middle point between the true backend architecture and the front end UI, it gives us a clean layer to avoid the UI directly talking to multiple places. 

Responsibilities:
- receive requests from the UI
- apply basic application rules
- communicate with the database
- communicate with the external API 
- return useful responses to the UI

### Database
Store's culture engines own data. 

Responsibilities:
- Store watched films
- store user ratings
- store local film records

### External Movie API
A third party movie database used for film name search and validation.

Responsibilities:
- provide film search results
- provide basic film metadata

